        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the flour, yeast, salt, and sugar in a bowl. Add the cold milk, egg, and soft butter and mix to a smooth dough. Knead briefly (5 minutes), shape into a rectangle, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Laminate the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll the chilled dough into a rectangle roughly twice the size of the butter block. Place the butter block in the centre, fold the dough over it, and seal the edges. Roll out to a long rectangle. Fold into thirds (like a letter), wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Repeat this roll, fold, and chill sequence twice more, for three folds total. After the final fold, refrigerate for at least 1 hour before shaping.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape, prove, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, and lemon juice. Roll the laminated dough to about 5 mm thick and cut into 10 x 10 cm squares. Place a spoonful of cream cheese in the centre of each square and a small spoonful of raspberry jam on top. Fold two opposite corners to the centre, pressing firmly. Arrange on lined trays, cover loosely, and prove for 60 minutes until puffed. Heat the oven to 200°C conventional (180°C fan). Brush with egg wash and bake for 20 to 25 minutes until deep golden. Drizzle with icing sugar glaze once cooled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
